Description.SourceString: An unusual glyph that hints at a mystery within.
An activated glyph, buzzing with a dangerous energy.
A temporarily stable glyph, opening to something far beyond our understanding.
A glyph overwhelmed with unstable energy, breaking under the weight of existence.
A keychain that Ace used as a card guard during one of his biggest Texas hold'em scores.
It's a stopwatch that takes its name far too literally.
Uh, Oh's Pub & Grill is the place to be for off-beat and unusual Vegas bets.
Fast out of the gates, Meg's sprint burst earned her a shiny gold medal.
If you ever need an ace up your sleeve, here's three.
Run while the bell tolls, run o soul forsaken.
In the ashes, the embers burn red hot.
A well-used grill smelling of blood and meat.
A melancholy image of sandals, worn during simpler, care-free days.
An uninhabited shell like many others, yet spectacular nonetheless.
And this is why you don't open cans of worms.
General wisdom states that a can of worms should never be opened, yet here we are.
A stalk of wood vastly improved with the addition of high sugar treats.
We'll wreck anything you bring in—no questions asked.
What appears as a benign symbol can hold the very power of death.
It's a wrecked car or, from another point of view, an affordable coffin made of reliable American steel.
A refreshing summer beverage that carries a terrible curse.
In these restraints her spirit broke, until all that remained was a terrible hunger.
For all the trauma that existed in the world, he was still a child with childish hopes.
When the men came, he only knew to do one thing—hide.
He killed the men for what they did. He made them howl in pain.
He wanted to believe that things in a new land could be better.
Wrath overcame him, but even then he resisted—until something unknown, something unnatural, twisted him.
She moved fast through the alleys, but how far could speed take her?
She had a lot to learn before the track meet and not a lot of time to learn it.
She might just be the fastest in her school, but she'd have to prove it.
She was so close to her goal, but an injury stopped her dead in her tracks.
She gritted her teeth through injury and persevered over all.
